article.headline: Coastal Carolina 73, Liberty 58
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Joseph Harris and Mario Edwards each had double-doubles to lead Coastal Carolina to a 73-58 victory over Liberty on Saturday night. Harris had 16 points and 12 rebounds for his seventh double-double in nine games and Edwards scored 16 points with 10 rebounds as the Chanticleers (7-2, 2-0 Big South Conference) extended their winning streak to three games. Coastal Carolina, which is 2-0 in the Big South for the first time since 2006-07, is off to its best start since 1981-82. Coastal Carolina led by as many as 14 points in the first half and increased its advantage to 41-25 on Edwards' layup with 19:12 left in the game. Harris hit a jumper 29 seconds later for a 43-25 lead. Chad Gray, who finished with 16 points, scored six straight points to give Liberty a 54-30 lead with 13:21 left. Kyle Ohman led Liberty (4-5, 1-1) with 17 points and Jesse Sanders added 12 points.
